      "id": 1,
      "text": "Tangelo Park sprang up in the 1950s as one of Orlando’s first post‑WWII suburbs, named after the tangelo citrus hybrid that once grew locally.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.trawellino.com/destinations/united-states/florida_tangelo-park"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Originally built to house workers at nearby missile testing grounds, Tangelo Park grew into a residential enclave surrounded by big‑box stores and tourist spots.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangelo_Park%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 1993, philanthropist Harris Rosen adopted Tangelo Park, providing free preschool and funding college education for local high‑school graduates.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        22
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangelo_Park%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "By 2013, Rosen had donated about $10 million to the community, helping transform it into a family‑friendly neighborhood.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangelo_Park%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Tangelo Park lies close to Universal Studios and Walt Disney World, yet remains a distinct, affordable residential area.",
